	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_70567"><p>I think the idea is sufficiently old. Umberto Eco details various attempts made during the years in his book <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Search-Perfect-Language-Making-Europe/dp/0631174656" title="amazon.com" rel="nofollow">The Search for a Perfect Language</a> [amazon.com]. Newspeak in <a href="http://www.amazon.com/1984-60th-Anniversary-Plume-George-Orwell/dp/0452262933" title="amazon.com" rel="nofollow">1984</a> [amazon.com] has words selectively pruned from it so that dangerous thought becomes difficult or impossible.</p></div>
		
	
	</div>
	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_70567"></div>

</div>


<div id="replyto_70567"></div>

