	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_69325"><p>According to <a href="http://perlcabal.org/syn/S32/IO.html#IO%3A%3AFileNode" title="perlcabal.org" rel="nofollow">S32/IO</a> [perlcabal.org], the return type of <code>slurp</code> (which reads a whole file at once) is <code>Str|Buf</code>. A <code>Buf</code> is returned when a parameter<nobr> <wbr></nobr><code>:bin</code> is passed to <code>slurp</code>. After that, you can treat the <code>Buf</code> you get as an array (because <code>Buf does Positional</code>, and do as advanced indexing operations as you need to find your byte sequence.</p><p>I wish I could show this with real, working code, but <code>Buf</code> isn't implemented just yet in Rakudo.</p></div>
		
	
	</div>
	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_69325"></div>

