		<div id="comment_body_69330"><p>The spec is a bit silent on that point, so I <a href="http://irclog.perlgeek.de/perl6/2009-07-07#i_1294238" title="perlgeek.de" rel="nofollow">asked on #perl6</a> [perlgeek.de]. The conclusion seems to be "convert it to a string if you want to pattern match".</p><p>Then again, if smartmatching with list semantics is what you're after, that should work. Something like <code>$buf ~~ (*, 104, 101, 108, 108, 111, *)</code> to find "hello" in an ASCII-encoded Buf.</p></div>
		
	
