	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_69402">There are (at least) two things wrong with Java's encoding support:

<ol>
<li>No way to avoid UnsupportedEncodingException, even for UTF-8, which is guaranteed to be present.</li><li>The concept of a "system default encoding" is flawed and leads to bugs in portability.  You should be forced to always specify an encoding.</li></ol></div>
		
	
	</div>
	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_69402"></div>

